# Quasar global theme opt-out

Global rules in `src/css/app.scss` force blue styling on most Quasar selects and menus (e.g. `.q-select:not(.use-default)`).

When a component needs custom or group-based colors on `q-select`, `q-menu`, or select popups:

1. Add class **`use-default`** on the control (`q-select` / `q-menu`).
2. For `q-select` dropdowns, also set `popup-content-class="use-default …"`.
3. Style locally via CSS variables on a parent container:

**Field (q-select.use-default):** `--co21-field-fg`, `--co21-field-bg`, `--co21-field-border`, `--co21-field-border-focus`, `--co21-field-placeholder`

**Popup (q-menu.use-default / q-select__popup.use-default):** `--co21-menu-bg`, `--co21-menu-fg`, `--co21-menu-placeholder`

Without `use-default`, global `!important` rules (blue field, green border, white popup text) override component styles.
